@DATABASE "Last Ninja 2"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - L - Last Ninja 2"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - L
                   ====================================

                               Last Ninja 2
                               ============



DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(29966,255)"}          29966,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(40777,0)"}          40777,0
@{"Level One     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(36576,198)"}          36576,198
@{"Level Two     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(35993,198)"}          35993,198
@{"Level Three   " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(36751,198)"}          36751,198

                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         I haven't tested this one as I don't have the
                         game :(

                         Rastan
@endnode
